The paper deals with the development of an index structure for efficient processing of complex spatial keyword queries, which involves the integration of spatial and non-spatial attributes. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). However, since the paper focuses primarily on the optimization of query processing, cs.DB and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
